column4: private void __parsePassiveModeReply(String reply)<sep>      throws MalformedServerReplyException {<sep>    int i@& index@& lastIndex;<sep>    String octet1@& octet2;<sep>    StringBuffer host;<sep><sep>    reply = reply.substring(reply.indexOf('(') + 1@& reply.indexOf(')')).trim();<sep><sep>    host = new StringBuffer(24);<sep>    lastIndex = 0;<sep>    index = reply.indexOf('@&');<sep>    host.append(reply.substring(lastIndex@& index));<sep><sep>    for (i = 0; i < 3; i++) {<sep>      host.append('.');<sep>      lastIndex = index + 1;<sep>      index = reply.indexOf('@&'@& lastIndex);<sep>      host.append(reply.substring(lastIndex@& index));<sep>    }<sep><sep>    lastIndex = index + 1;<sep>    index = reply.indexOf('@&'@& lastIndex);<sep><sep>    octet1 = reply.substring(lastIndex@& index);<sep>    octet2 = reply.substring(index + 1);<sep><sep>    // index and lastIndex now used as temporaries<sep>    try {<sep>      index = Integer.parseInt(octet1);<sep>      lastIndex = Integer.parseInt(octet2);<sep>    } catch (NumberFormatException e) {<sep>      throw new MalformedServerReplyException(<sep>          "Could not parse passive host information. changelines Server Reply: " + reply);<sep>    }<sep><sep>    index <<= 8;<sep>    index |= lastIndex;<sep><sep>    __passiveHost = host.toString();<sep>    __passivePort = index;<sep>  }

column4: private void addOwners(NaryJoin node@& List<Owned<NaryJoin>> ows@& List<LocalJoin> vars) throws RepositoryException {<sep>		boolean local = isLocal(vars);<sep>		if (ows.size() == 1) {<sep>			RepositoryConnection owner = ows.get(0).getOwner();<sep>			if (owner == null) {<sep>				// every element has multiple owners<sep>				if (local) {<sep>					performReplacementsInNode(node@& vars);<sep>				}<sep>			} else {<sep>				// every element is used by the same owner<sep>				node.replaceWith(new OwnedTupleExpr(owner@& node.clone()));<sep>			}<sep>		} else if (local) {<sep>			AbstractQueryModelNode replacement = new NaryJoin();<sep>			for (LocalJoin v : vars) {<sep>				Var var = v.getVar();<sep>				NaryJoin join = v.getJoin();<sep>				if (var == null) {<sep>					// each of these arguments could be anywhere<sep>					for (TupleExpr expr : join.getArgs()) {<sep>						((NaryJoin) replacement).addArg(expr);<sep>					}<sep>				} else {<sep>					replacement = optimizeReplacementJoin(replacement@& join);<sep>				}<sep>			}<sep>			node.replaceWith(replacement);<sep>		} else {<sep>			NaryJoin replacement = generateReplacementFromOwnedJoins(ows);<sep>			node.replaceWith(replacement);<sep>		}<sep>	}

private AQPair test(BigInteger A@& BigInteger Q@& int x) { // sign BigInteger Q_rest = Q; if (Q.signum() < 0) { smallFactors.add(-1); Q_rest = Q.negate(); } // Remove multiples of 2 int lsb = Q_rest.getLowestSetBit(); if (lsb > 0) { smallFactors.add(2@& (short)lsb); Q_rest = Q_rest.shiftRight(lsb); } // Unsieved prime base elements are added directly to pass 2. int pass2Count = 0; for (; pass2Count pass2Primes[pass2Count] = unsievedBaseElements[pass2Count]; pass2Powers[pass2Count] = unsievedBaseElements[pass2Count]; pass2Exponents[pass2Count] = 1; } // Pass 1: Test solution arrays ("re-sieving"). // Starting at the biggest prime base elements is faster because then Q_rest is reduced quicker in pass 2. // IMPORTANT: Java gives x % p = x for |x| < p@& and we have many p bigger than any sieve array entry. // IMPORTANT: Not computing the modulus in these cases improves performance by almost factor 2! int xAbs = Math.abs(x); for (int pIndex = baseSize-1; pIndex > 0; pIndex--) { // p[0]=2 was already tested int p = powers[pIndex]; int xModP = xAbs

if (xModP<0) xModP += p; // make remainder non-negative for negative x// if (DEBUG) {// if (xModP<0) LOG.debug("x=" + x + "@& p=" + p + " -> x % p = " + xModP + "@& x1 = " + x1Array[pIndex] + "@& x2 = " + x2Array[pIndex]);// assertTrue(0<=xModP && xModP// } if (xModP==x1Array[pIndex] || xModP==x2Array[pIndex]) { pass2Primes[pass2Count] = primes[pIndex]; pass2Exponents[pass2Count] = exponents[pIndex]; pass2Powers[pass2Count++] = p; // for some reasons I do not understand it is faster to divide Q by p in pass 2 only@& not here } } // Pass 2: Reduce Q by the pass2Primes and collect small factors Q_rest_UBI.set(Q_rest); for (int pass2Index = 0; pass2Index < pass2Count; pass2Index++) { int p = pass2Powers[pass2Index]; while (true) { int rem = Q_rest_UBI.divideAndRemainder(p@& quotient_UBI); if (rem>0) break; // remainder == 0 -> the division was exact. assign quotient to Q_rest and add p to factors UnsignedBigInt tmp = Q_rest_UBI; Q_rest_UBI = quotient_UBI; quotient_UBI = tmp; smallFactors.add(pass2Primes[pass2Index]@& (short)pass2Exponents[pass2Index]);// if (DEBUG) {// BigInteger pBig = BigInteger.valueOf(p);// BigInteger[] div = Q_rest.divideAndRemainder(pBig);// assertEquals(div[1].intValue()@& rem);// Q_rest = div[0];// } } } if (Q_rest_UBI.isOne()) return new Smooth_Perfect(A@& smallFactors); Q_rest = Q_rest_UBI.toBigInteger(); // Division by all p<=pMax was not sufficient to factor Q completely. // The remaining Q_rest is either a prime > pMax@& or a composite > pMax^2. if (Q_rest.bitLength()>31 || Q_rest.doubleValue() >= maxQRest) return null; // Q is not sufficiently smooth // Note: We could as well use pMax^c with c~1.75 as threshold. Larger factors do not help to find smooth congruences. // Q is sufficiently smooth if (DEBUG) LOG.debug("Sufficient smooth big factor = " + Q_rest); return new Partial_1Large(A@& smallFactors@& Q_rest.intValue()); }

i < szSources ; i++) {<sep>            if (i == firstIndex) {<sep>                continue;<sep>            }<sep><sep>            RegisterSpec rs = sources.get(i);<sep><sep>            // Just skip void (unresolved phi results) for now<sep>            if (rs.getBasicType() == Type.BT_VOID){<sep>                continue;<sep>            }<sep><sep>            sameLocals = sameLocals<sep>                    && equalsHandlesNulls(firstLocal@& rs.getLocalItem());<sep><sep>            mergedType = Merger.mergeType(mergedType@& rs.getType());<sep>        }<sep><sep>        TypeBearer newResultType;<sep><sep>        if (mergedType != null) {<sep>            newResultType = mergedType;<sep>        } else {<sep>            StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();<sep><sep>            for (int i = 0; column4: private void visitTree(StopSelectionTreeBean tree@&<sep>      StopSelectionBean selection@& List<Integer> selectionIndices@& int index)<sep>      throws InvalidSelectionServiceException {<sep><sep>    // If we have a stop@& we have no choice but to return<sep>    if (tree.hasStop()) {<sep>      selection.setStop(tree.getStop());<sep>      return;<sep>    }<sep><sep>    Set<NameBean> names = tree.getNames();<sep><sep>    // If we've only got one name@& short circuit<sep>    if (names.size() == 1) {<sep><sep>      NameBean next = names.iterator().next();<sep>      selection.addSelected(next);<sep><sep>      StopSelectionTreeBean subtree = tree.getSubTree(next);<sep>      visitTree(subtree@& selection@& selectionIndices@& index);<sep><sep>      return;<sep>    }<sep><sep>    if (index >= selectionIndices.size()) {<sep><sep>      for (NameBean name : names) {<sep>        StopBean stop = getStop(tree.getSubTree(name));<sep>        if (stop != null) {<sep>          selection.addNameWithStop(name@& stop);<sep>        } else {<sep>          selection.addName(name);<sep>        }<sep>      }<sep><sep>      List<StopBean> stops = tree.getAllStops();<sep><sep>      for (StopBean stop : stops)<sep>        selection.addStop(stop);<sep><sep>      return;<sep>    } else {<sep><sep>      int i = 0;<sep>      int selectionIndex = selectionIndices.get(index);<sep><sep>      for (NameBean name : names) {<sep>        if (selectionIndex == i) {<sep>          selection.addSelected(name);<sep>          tree = tree.getSubTree(name);<sep>          visitTree(tree@& selection@& selectionIndices@& index + 1);<sep>          return;<sep>        }<sep>        i++;<sep>      }<sep>    }<sep><sep>    // If we made it here...<sep>    throw new InvalidSelectionServiceException();<sep>  }

column4: public int convertToAbsoluteDirection(int flags@& int layoutDirection) {<sep>            int masked = flags & RELATIVE_DIR_FLAGS;<sep>            if (masked == 0) {<sep>                return flags; // does not have any relative flags@& good.<sep>            }<sep>            flags &= ~masked; //remove start / end<sep>            if (layoutDirection == View.LAYOUT_DIRECTION_LTR) {<sep>                // no change. just OR with 2 bits shifted mask and return<sep>                flags |= masked >> 2; // START is 2 bits after LEFT@& END is 2 bits after RIGHT.<sep>                return flags;<sep>            } else {<sep>                // add START flag as RIGHT<sep>                flags |= ((masked >> 1) & ~RELATIVE_DIR_FLAGS);<sep>                // first clean start bit then add END flag as LEFT<sep>                flags |= ((masked >> 1) & RELATIVE_DIR_FLAGS) >> 2;<sep>            }<sep>            return flags;<sep>        }

column4: public String reindent(String code) {<sep>    try {<sep>      // Remove indention from each line.<sep>      StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();<sep>      LineReader lr = new LineReader(new StringReader(code));<sep>      String line = lr.readLine();<sep>      while (line != null) {<sep>        sb.append(line.trim());<sep>        line = lr.readLine();<sep>        if (line != null) {<sep>          sb.append(' changelines ');<sep>        }<sep>      }<sep>      String strippedCode = sb.toString();<sep><sep>      // Now indent it again.<sep>      int indent = indention * DEFAULT_INDENTION;<sep>      sb.setLength(0);  // reset buffer<sep>      lr = new LineReader(new StringReader(strippedCode));<sep>      line = lr.readLine();<sep>      while (line != null) {<sep>        if (line.startsWith("}")) {<sep>          indent -= DEFAULT_INDENTION;<sep>        }<sep>        if (!line.startsWith("#line")) {<sep>          sb.append(pad(indent));<sep>        }<sep>        sb.append(line);<sep>        if (line.endsWith("{")) {<sep>          indent += DEFAULT_INDENTION;<sep>        }<sep>        line = lr.readLine();<sep>        if (line != null) {<sep>          sb.append(' changelines ');<sep>        }<sep>      }<sep>      return sb.toString();<sep>    } catch (IOException e) {<sep>      // Should never happen with string readers.<sep>      throw new AssertionError(e);<sep>    }<sep>  }

lessonItem.setLink(lesson.getLink());<sep>                lessonItem.setType(LessonMenuItemType.LESSON);<sep>                if (lesson.isCompleted(ws)) {<sep> (Category.CHALLENGE.equals(lesson.getCategory())) {<sep>                    lessonItem.setShowHints(lesson.isAuthorized(ws@& AbstractLesson.CHALLENGE_ROLE@& WebSession.SHOWHINTS));<sep>                    lessonItem.setShowSource(lesson.isAuthorized(ws@& AbstractLesson.CHALLENGE_ROLE@& WebSession.SHOWHINTS));<sep>                }<sep><sep>                categoryItem.addChild(lessonItem);<sep> column4: public void actionDeleteCascade() throws JspException {<sep><sep>        // save initialized instance of this class in request attribute for included sub-elements<sep>        getJsp().getRequest().setAttribute(SESSION_WORKPLACE_CLASS@& this);<sep>        try {<sep>            // list of all resources containing this propertydefinition<sep>            List resourcesWithProperty = getCms().readResourcesWithProperty(getParamPropertyName());<sep>            // list of all resources locked by another user@& containing this propertydefinition<sep>            List resourcesLockedByOtherUser = getResourcesLockedByOtherUser(resourcesWithProperty);<sep>            // do the following operations only if all of the resources are not locked by another user<sep>            if (resourcesLockedByOtherUser.isEmpty()) {<sep>                // save the site root<sep>                String storedSiteRoot = getCms().getRequestContext().getSiteRoot();<sep>                try {<sep>                    // change to the root site<sep>                    getCms().getRequestContext().setSiteRoot("/");<sep><sep>                    Iterator i = resourcesWithProperty.iterator();<sep>                    while (i.hasNext()) {<sep>                        CmsResource resource = (CmsResource)i.next();<sep>                        // read the property object<sep>                        CmsProperty property = getCms().readPropertyObject(<sep>                            resource.getRootPath()@&<sep>                            getParamPropertyName()@&<sep>                            false);<sep>                        // try to delete the property if it is not the NULL PROPERTY<sep>                        // if the property is the NULL PROPERTY@& it only had a shared<sep>                        // value which was deleted at a sibling which was already processed<sep>                        if (!property.isNullProperty()) {<sep>                            CmsLock lock = getCms().getLock(resource);<sep>                            if (lock.isUnlocked()) {<sep>                                // lock the resource for the current (Admin) user<sep>                                getCms().lockResource(resource.getRootPath());<sep>                            }<sep>                            property.setStructureValue(CmsProperty.DELETE_VALUE);<sep>                            property.setResourceValue(CmsProperty.DELETE_VALUE);<sep>                            // write the property with the null value to the resource and cascade it from the definition<sep>                            getCms().writePropertyObject(resource.getRootPath()@& property);<sep>                            // unlock the resource<sep>                            getCms().unlockResource(resource.getRootPath());<sep>                        }<sep>                    }<sep>                    // delete the property definition at last<sep>                    getCms().deletePropertyDefinition(getParamPropertyName());<sep>                } finally {<sep>                    // restore the siteroot<sep>                    getCms().getRequestContext().setSiteRoot(storedSiteRoot);<sep>                    // close the dialog<sep>                    actionCloseDialog();<sep>                }<sep>            } else {<sep><sep>                StringBuffer reason = new StringBuffer();<sep>                reason.append(dialogWhiteBoxStart());<sep>                reason.append(buildResourceList(resourcesLockedByOtherUser@& true));<sep>                reason.append(dialogWhiteBoxEnd());<sep>                throw new CmsVfsException(<sep>                    Messages.get().container(Messages.ERR_DEL_PROP_RESOURCES_LOCKED_1@& reason.toString()));<sep>            }<sep>        } catch (Throwable e) {<sep>            // error while deleting property definition@& show error dialog<sep>            includeErrorpage(this@& e);<sep>        }<sep>    }

column4: public int maxKilledEnemies(char[][] grid) {<sep>    if (grid == null) {<sep>      return 0;<sep>    }<sep>    int m = grid.length;<sep>    int n = m == 0 ? 0 : grid[0].length;<sep>    int maxEnemies = 0;<sep>    int rowHits = 0;<sep>    int[] colHits = new int[n];<sep>    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {<sep>      for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {<sep>        if (grid[i][j] == WALL) { // Note that WALL can be skipped.<sep>          continue;<sep>        }<sep>        if (j == 0 || grid[i][j - 1] == WALL) {<sep>          rowHits = 0;<sep>          for (int k = j; k < n && grid[i][k] != WALL; k++) {<sep>            if (grid[i][k] == ENEMY) {<sep>              rowHits++;<sep>            }<sep>          }<sep>        }<sep>        if (i == 0 || grid[i - 1][j] == WALL) {<sep>          colHits[j] = 0;<sep>          for (int k = i; k < m && grid[k][j] != WALL; k++) {<sep>            if (grid[k][j] == ENEMY) {<sep>              colHits[j]++;<sep>            }<sep>          }<sep>        }<sep>        if (grid[i][j] == EMPTY) { // Only update when the cell is empty.<sep>          maxEnemies = Integer.max(rowHits + colHits[j]@& maxEnemies);<sep>        }<sep>      }<sep>    }<sep>    return maxEnemies;<sep>  }

column4: public FuzzyBoolean matches(ResolvedType[] someArgs) {<sep>		// do some quick length tests first<sep>		int numArgsMatchedByEllipsis = (someArgs.length + ellipsisCount) - typePatterns.length;<sep>		if (numArgsMatchedByEllipsis < 0) {<sep>			return FuzzyBoolean.NO;<sep>		}<sep>		if ((numArgsMatchedByEllipsis > 0) && (ellipsisCount == 0)) {<sep>			return FuzzyBoolean.NO;<sep>		}<sep>		// now work through the args and the patterns@& skipping at ellipsis<sep>		FuzzyBoolean ret = FuzzyBoolean.YES;<sep>		int argsIndex = 0;<sep>		for (int i = 0; i < typePatterns.length; i++) {<sep>			if (typePatterns[i] == AnnotationTypePattern.ELLIPSIS) {<sep>				// match ellipsisMatchCount args<sep>				argsIndex += numArgsMatchedByEllipsis;<sep>			} else if (typePatterns[i] == AnnotationTypePattern.ANY) {<sep>				argsIndex++;<sep>			} else {<sep>				// match the argument type at argsIndex with the ExactAnnotationTypePattern<sep>				// we know it is exact because nothing else is allowed in args<sep>				if (someArgs[argsIndex].isPrimitiveType()) {<sep>					return FuzzyBoolean.NO; // can never match<sep>				}<sep>				ExactAnnotationTypePattern ap = (ExactAnnotationTypePattern) typePatterns[i];<sep>				FuzzyBoolean matches = ap.matchesRuntimeType(someArgs[argsIndex]);<sep>				if (matches == FuzzyBoolean.NO) {<sep>					return FuzzyBoolean.MAYBE; // could still match at runtime<sep>				} else {<sep>					argsIndex++;<sep>					ret = ret.and(matches);<sep>				}<sep>			}<sep>		}<sep>		return ret;<sep>	}

public static int processLoginRequest(Channel channel@& Msg msg@& DecodeIterator decIter@& Error error) throws UnknownHostException { MsgKey requestKey = null; int retCode; ElementList elementList = CodecFactory.createElementList(); ElementEntry element = CodecFactory.createElementEntry(); /* Switch cases depending on message class */ switch (msg.msgClass()) { case MsgClasses.REQUEST: { /* get request message key - retrieve the MsgKey structure from the provided decoded message structure */ requestKey = msg.msgKey(); /* check if key has user name */ /* user name is only login user type accepted by this application (user name is the default type) */ if (((requestKey.flags() & MsgKeyFlags.HAS_NAME) == 0) || (((requestKey.flags() & MsgKeyFlags.HAS_NAME_TYPE) != 0) && (requestKey.nameType() != Login.UserIdTypes.NAME))) { if ((retCode = sendLoginRequestRejectStatusMsg(channel@& msg.streamId()@& LoginRejectReason.NO_USER_NAME_IN_REQUEST)) != TransportReturnCodes.SUCCESS) { return TransportReturnCodes.FAILURE; } break; } if (loginRequestInfo_IsInUse && (loginRequestInfo_StreamId != msg.streamId())) { if ((retCode = sendLoginRequestRejectStatusMsg(channel@& msg.streamId()@& LoginRejectReason.MAX_LOGIN_REQUESTS_REACHED)) != TransportReturnCodes.SUCCESS) { return TransportReturnCodes.FAILURE; } break; } /* decode login request */ /* get StreamId */ loginRequestInfo_StreamId = msg.streamId(); loginRequestInfo_IsInUse = true; /* get Username */ if (requestKey.name().data() == null) { loginRequestInfo_Username = null; } else { loginRequestInfo_Username = requestKey.name().toString(); } /* decode key opaque data */ /** * @brief Allows the user to continue decoding of any message * key attributes with the same changelinesr ef DecodeIterator used * when calling DecodeMsg * * Typical use:
* 1. Call DecodeMsg()
* 2. If there are any message key attributes and the * application wishes to decode them using the same changelinesr ef * DecodeIterator@& call decodeKeyAttrib() and continue * decoding using the appropriate container type decode * functions@& as indicated by * MsgKey::attribContainerType
* 3. If payload is present and the application wishes to * decode it@& use the appropriate decode functions@& as * specified in changelinesr ef MsgBase::containerType
*/ if ((retCode = msg.decodeKeyAttrib(decIter@& requestKey)) != CodecReturnCodes.SUCCESS) { return TransportReturnCodes.FAILURE; } /* decode element list */ /** * @brief Decodes an ElementList container * * Typical use:
* 1. Call elementList.decode()
* 2. Call ElementEntry.decode until error or * ::END_OF_CONTAINER is returned.
*/ if ((retCode = elementList.decode(decIter@& null)) == CodecReturnCodes.SUCCESS) { /* decode each element entry in list */ while ((retCode = element.decode(decIter)) != CodecReturnCodes.END_OF_CONTAINER) { /* get login request information */ if (retCode == CodecReturnCodes.SUCCESS) { /* ApplicationId */ if (element.name().equals(ElementNames.APPID)) { loginRequestInfo_ApplicationId = element.encodedData().toString(); } /* ApplicationName */ else if (element.name().equals(ElementNames.APPNAME)) { loginRequestInfo_ApplicationName = element.encodedData().toString(); } /* Position */ else if (element.name().equals(ElementNames.POSITION)) { loginRequestInfo_Position = element.encodedData().toString(); } /* Password */ else if (element.name().equals(ElementNames.PASSWORD)) { loginRequestInfo_Password = element.encodedData().toString(); } /* InstanceId */ else if (element.name().equals(ElementNames.INST_ID)) { loginRequestInfo_InstanceId = element.encodedData().toString(); } /* Role */ else if (element.name().equals(ElementNames.ROLE)) { loginRequestInfo_Role = element.encodedData().toString(); } } else { return TransportReturnCodes.FAILURE; } } } else { return TransportReturnCodes.FAILURE; } System.out.printf("Received Login Request for Username: %s changelines "@& loginRequestInfo_Username); /* send login response */ if ((retCode = sendLoginResponse(channel)) != TransportReturnCodes.SUCCESS) { return retCode; } } break; case MsgClasses.CLOSE: { System.out.printf("Received Login Close for StreamId %d changelines "@& msg.streamId()); /* close login stream */ closeLoginStream(msg.streamId()); } break; default: { System.out.printf("Received Unhandled Login Msg Class: %d changelines "@& msg.msgClass()); return TransportReturnCodes.FAILURE; } } return TransportReturnCodes.SUCCESS; }

column4: public static void main(final String[] args) {<sep>        //@TODO This method should be moved to a meaningful example class that creates Cloudlets instead of customers<sep><sep>        /*<sep>         * Mean number of customers that arrives per minute.<sep>         * The value of 0.4 customers per minute means that 1 customer will arrive<sep>         * at every 2.5 minutes.<sep>         * It means that 1 minute / 0.4 customer per minute = 1 customer at every 2.5 minutes.<sep>         * This is the inter-arrival time (in average).<sep>         */<sep>        final double MEAN_CUSTOMERS_ARRIVAL_MINUTE = 0.4;<sep><sep>        /*<sep>         * Time length of each simulation in minutes.<sep>         */<sep>        final int SIMULATION_TIME_LENGTH = 25;<sep><sep>        //If the arrival of each customers must be shown.<sep>        final boolean showCustomerArrivals = true;<sep><sep>        /*<sep>         * Number of simulations to run.<sep>         */<sep>        final int NUMBER_OF_SIMULATIONS = 100;<sep><sep>        final BiConsumer<PoissonDistr@& Integer> printArrivals = (poisson@& minute) -> {<sep>            if (showCustomerArrivals) {<sep>                System.out.printf("%d customers arrived at minute %d%n"@& poisson.getK()@& minute);<sep>            }<sep>        };<sep><sep>        /**<sep>         * A {@link Function} to simulate the arrival of customers for a given time period.<sep>         * This is just a method to test the implementation.<sep>         *<sep>         * @param poisson the PoissonDistr object that will compute the customer arrivals probabilities<sep>         * @return the number of arrived customers<sep>         */<sep>        final Function<PoissonDistr@& Integer> runSimulation = poisson -> {<sep>            /*We want to check the probability of 1 customer to arrive at each<sep>            single minute. The default k value is 1@& so we dont need to set it.*/<sep>            final int totalArrivedCustomers =<sep>                IntStream.range(0@& SIMULATION_TIME_LENGTH)<sep>                    .filter(time -> poisson.eventsHappened())<sep>                    .peek(time -> printArrivals.accept(poisson@& time))<sep>                    .map(time -> poisson.getK())<sep>                    .sum();<sep><sep>            System.out.printf(<sep>                "	%d customers arrived in %d minutes%n"@& totalArrivedCustomers@& SIMULATION_TIME_LENGTH);<sep>            System.out.printf(<sep>                "	Arrival rate: %.2f customers per minute. Customers inter-arrival time: %.2f minutes in average%n"@&<sep>                poisson.getLambda()@& poisson.getInterArrivalMeanTime());<sep><sep>            return totalArrivedCustomers;<sep>        };<sep><sep>        double customersInAllSimulations = 0;<sep>        PoissonDistr poisson = null;<sep>        final long seed = System.currentTimeMillis();<sep>        for (int i = 0; i < NUMBER_OF_SIMULATIONS; i++) {<sep>            poisson = new PoissonDistr(MEAN_CUSTOMERS_ARRIVAL_MINUTE@& seed + i);<sep>            System.out.printf("Simulation number %d%n"@& i);<sep>            customersInAllSimulations += runSimulation.apply(poisson);<sep>        }<sep><sep>        final double mean = customersInAllSimulations / NUMBER_OF_SIMULATIONS;<sep>        System.out.printf("%nArrived customers average after %d simulations: %.2f%n"@&<sep>            NUMBER_OF_SIMULATIONS@& mean);<sep>        System.out.printf(<sep>            "%.2f customers expected by each %d minutes of simulation with inter-arrival time of %.2f minutes%n"@&<sep>            poisson.getLambda() * SIMULATION_TIME_LENGTH@& SIMULATION_TIME_LENGTH@&<sep>            poisson.getInterArrivalMeanTime());<sep>    }

column4: private static String replaceInstructionStringWithTransMap( String inst@& HashMap<Byte@&Byte> transMap )<sep>	{<sep>		//prevent unnecessary parsing and reconstruction<sep>		if( inst == null || inst.isEmpty() || transMap.isEmpty() )<sep>			return inst;<sep>		<sep>		String[] pinst = inst.split(Lop.INSTRUCTION_DELIMITOR);<sep>		StringBuilder instOut = new StringBuilder();<sep>		for( String lpinst : pinst ){ //for each instruction<sep>			//split instruction into parts<sep>			String[] parts = InstructionUtils.getInstructionPartsWithValueType(lpinst);<sep>			//replace instruction parts<sep>			for( int i=0; i<parts.length; i++ )<sep>			{<sep>				String lpart = parts[i];<sep>				int pos = lpart.indexOf(Instruction.DATATYPE_PREFIX+DataType.MATRIX.toString());<sep>				if( pos>0 ){<sep>					String index = lpart.substring(0@& pos);	<sep>					String newindex = String.valueOf(transMap.get(Byte.parseByte(index)));<sep>					parts[i] = newindex + lpart.substring(pos); <sep>				}<sep>			}<sep>			<sep>			if( instOut.length()>0 )<sep>				instOut.append(Lop.INSTRUCTION_DELIMITOR);<sep>			<sep>			//reconstruct instruction<sep>			instOut.append("MR");<sep>			for( String lpart : parts ){<sep>				instOut.append(Lop.OPERAND_DELIMITOR);<sep>				instOut.append(lpart);<sep>			}<sep>		}<sep>		<sep>		return instOut.toString();<sep>	}

column4: private int readBigEndianModifiedBase128Number(ByteBuffer bb) {<sep>        int i = 0;<sep><sep>        this.tempbytesread = 0;<sep>        byte b = bb.get();<sep>        tempbytesread++;<sep>        // get the lower 7 bits of b into i<sep>        i = b & 0x7F;<sep>        while ((b & 0x80) > 0) {<sep>            // while the top bit of b is set (the "more" bit)<sep>            // get another byte<sep>            b = bb.get();<sep>            tempbytesread++;<sep>            // left shift i by 7 bits@& making sure the top bit ends up being set@& and bitwise OR<sep>            // this with the lower 7 bits of i. Put the result in i.<sep>            // in other words@& left shift in 7 more bits of data from b into i!<sep>            i = ((i + 1) << 7) | (b & 0x7F);<sep>        }<sep>        return i;<sep>    }

// Really want rounding toward 0.<sep>            } while (base == oldBase);<sep>        }<sep>    }

column4: public void testHeadToHeadFilters() {<sep>        // Each pair of strings contains an indexable query filter and a pattern that<sep>        // its index optimization's plan will contain in its "explain" output.<sep>        // The pairs are sorted in preference order@& so we can generally expect to find<sep>        // the pattern after planning a query with the filter by itself or in combination<sep>        // with any filter listed later. There are currently exceptions@& which are<sep>        // counted below as "surprises"@& which we hope will not regress (increase)<sep>        // as we evolve the cost calculations. The current costing does some particularly<sep>        // surprising things with the relative costing of plans for predicates that<sep>        // generally combine use of single and/or double-ended range filters<sep>        // with unique and/or non-unique index filters@& especially for compound indexes.<sep>        String head_to_head_filters[][] = {<sep>                {"uniquehashable = ?"@& "HASHUNIQUEHASH" }@&<sep>                {"component1 = ? and component2unique = ?"@& "COMPOUNDUNIQUE"}@&<sep>                {"primarykey = ?"@& "its primary" }@&<sep>                // These commented out entries tend to cause too many non-deterministic<sep>                // plan choices based on the order of planning same-cost plans.<sep>                //TODO: In some or all of these cases@& we may want to think about adding<sep>                // tie-breaker criteria to the cost calculations@& BUT this COULD cause<sep>                // backward incompatible plan choices that@& in actual effect@&<sep>                // could result in accidental performance regressions for existing<sep>                // applications that were already (empirically) tuned to rely on lucky<sep>                // breaks rather than deterministic costing.<sep>                // Long term@& the particular "tie" between unique key filtering and primary key<sep>                // filtering MAY OR MAY NOT be something we want to change:<sep>                // e.g. should "primary key" be favored over a "unique key" for exact<sep>                // equality filters@& but "unique key" preferred for non-equality<sep>                // filters? Should this preference be reversed when the unique key index<sep>                // is a hash index which must have been defined especially for equality<sep>                // filtering?<sep>                //<sep>                //{"uniquekey = ?"@& "POLYPOINTS_UNIQUEKEY" }@&<sep>                {"contains(poly@& ?)"@& "POINTSPOLY"}@&<sep>                {"component1 = ? and component2non = ?"@&"COMPOUNDNON" }@&<sep>                {"nonuniquekey = ?"@& "NONUNIQUE" }@&<sep>                {"component1 = ? and component2unique between ? and ?"@& "COMPOUNDUNIQUE" }@&<sep>                //{"primarykey between ? and ?"@& "its primary" }@&<sep>                {"uniquekey between ? and ?"@& "POLYPOINTS_UNIQUEKEY" }@&<sep>                //{"component1 = ? and component2non between ? and ?"@& "" }@&<sep>                {"nonuniquekey between ? and ?"@& "" }@&<sep>                {"component1 = ? and component2unique > ?"@& "" }@&<sep>                {"component1 = ? and component2non > ?"@& "COMPOUNDNON" }@&<sep>                {"primarykey > ?"@& "" }@&<sep>                {"uniquekey > ?"@& "UNIQUEKEY" }@&<sep>                {"nonuniquekey > ?"@& "" }@&<sep>        };<sep>        // Some number of "surprises" are deemed acceptable at least for now.<sep>        // The number was determined empirically as of V6.1.<sep>        final int ACCEPTABLE_SURPRISES = 5;<sep>        int surprises = 0;<sep>        StringBuffer surpriseDetails = new StringBuffer();<sep>        for (int ii = 0; ii < head_to_head_filters.length; ++ii) {<sep>            String[] filter1 = head_to_head_filters[ii];<sep>            for (int jj = ii+1; jj < head_to_head_filters.length; ++jj) {<sep>                String[] filter2 = head_to_head_filters[jj];<sep><sep>                AbstractPlanNode pn = compile(<sep>                        "select polys.point from polypoints polys " +<sep>                        "where " + filter1[0] + " and " + filter2[0] + " ;");<sep>                if (pn.toExplainPlanString().contains(filter1[1])) {<sep>                    /* enable to debug */System.out.println();<sep>                }<sep>                else {<sep>                    String detail = "The query filtered by " + filter1[0] +<sep>                            " AND " + filter2[0] + " is not using " +<sep>                            filter1[1] + " index.";<sep>                    surpriseDetails.append(detail).append(" changelines ");<sep>                    /* enable to debug */ System.out.println("WARNING: " + ii + " vs. " + jj + " " + detail);<sep>                    //* enable to debug */ System.out.println("DEBUG: " + ii + " vs. " + jj + " " + pn.toExplainPlanString());<sep>                    ++surprises;<sep>                }<sep>            }<sep>        }<sep>        if (surprises != ACCEPTABLE_SURPRISES) {<sep>            // Only report all of the surprise details when the number of surprises changes.<sep>            System.out.println("DEBUG: total plan surprises: " + surprises + " out of "<sep>                    + (head_to_head_filters.length * (head_to_head_filters.length-1)/2) + ".");<sep>            System.out.println(surpriseDetails);<sep>            if (surprises < ACCEPTABLE_SURPRISES) {<sep>                System.out.println("DEBUG: consider further constraining the baseline number to:");<sep>                System.out.println("        final int ACCEPTABLE_SURPRISES = " + surprises + ";");<sep>            }<sep>            // Only fail the test when the number of surprises goes up.<sep>            assertTrue(surprises < ACCEPTABLE_SURPRISES);<sep>        }<sep><sep>    }

column4: private static String makeLevelTwo(String segment) {<sep>        // Create a storage buffer for the result<sep>        StringBuilder result = new StringBuilder(segment.length() * 2);<sep><sep>        // Find all single tags<sep>        // Matcher match =<sep>        // Pattern.compile("<[a-zA-Z\-]+\d+/>").matcher(segment);<sep>        Matcher match = Pattern.compile("<[\S&&[^/\d]]+(\d+)/>").matcher(segment);<sep>        int previousMatchEnd = 0;<sep>        while (match.find()) {<sep>            // get the OmegaT tag and tag number<sep>            String tag = match.group();<sep>            String tagNumber = match.group(1);<sep><sep>            // Wrap the OmegaT tag in TMX tags in the result<sep>            result.append(segment.substring(previousMatchEnd@& match.start())); // text<sep>                                                                               // betw.<sep>                                                                               // prev.<sep>                                                                               // &<sep>                                                                               // cur.<sep>                                                                               // match<sep>            result.append("<ph x='"); // TMX start tag + i attribute<sep>            result.append(tagNumber); // OmegaT tag number used as x attribute<sep>            result.append("'>");<sep>            result.append(tag); // OmegaT tag<sep>            result.append("</ph>"); // TMX end tag<sep><sep>            // Store the current match's end positions<sep>            previousMatchEnd = match.end();<sep>        }<sep><sep>        // Append the text from the last match (single tag) to the end of the<sep>        // segment<sep>        result.append(segment.substring(previousMatchEnd@& segment.length()));<sep>        segment = result.toString(); // Store intermediate result back in<sep>                                     // segment<sep>        result.setLength(0); // Clear result buffer<sep><sep>        // Find all start tags<sep>        match = Pattern.compile("<[\S&&[^/\d]]+(\d+)>").matcher(segment);<sep>        previousMatchEnd = 0;<sep>        while (match.find()) {<sep>            // get the OmegaT tag and tag number<sep>            String tag = match.group();<sep>            String tagNumber = match.group(1);<sep><sep>            // Check if the corresponding end tag is in this segment too<sep>            String endTag = "</" + tag.substring(4);<sep>            boolean paired = segment.indexOf(endTag) > -1;<sep><sep>            // Wrap the OmegaT tag in TMX tags in the result<sep>            result.append(segment.substring(previousMatchEnd@& match.start())); // text<sep>                                                                               // betw.<sep>                                                                               // prev.<sep>                                                                               // &<sep>                                                                               // cur.<sep>                                                                               // match<sep>            if (paired) {<sep>                result.append("<bpt i='"); // TMX start tag + i attribute<sep>                result.append(tagNumber); // OmegaT tag number used as i<sep>                                          // attribute<sep>                result.append("'");<sep>            } else {<sep>                result.append("<it pos='begin'"); // TMX start tag<sep>            }<sep>            result.append(" x='"); // TMX x attribute<sep>            result.append(tagNumber); // OmegaT tag number used as x attribute<sep>            result.append("'>");<sep>            result.append(tag); // OmegaT tag<sep>            result.append(paired ? "</bpt>" : "</it>"); // TMX end tag<sep><sep>            // Store the current match's end positions<sep>            previousMatchEnd = match.end();<sep>        }<sep><sep>        // Append the text from the last match (start tag) to the end of the<sep>        // segment<sep>        result.append(segment.substring(previousMatchEnd@& segment.length()));<sep>        segment = result.toString(); // Store intermediate result back in<sep>                                     // segment<sep>        result.setLength(0); // Clear result buffer<sep><sep>        // Find all end tags<sep>        match = Pattern.compile("</[\S&&[^\d]]+(\d+)>").matcher(segment);<sep>        previousMatchEnd = 0;<sep>        while (match.find()) {<sep>            // get the OmegaT tag and tag number<sep>            String tag = match.group();<sep>            String tagNumber = match.group(1);<sep><sep>            // Check if the corresponding start tag is in this segment too<sep>            String startTag = "<" + tag.substring(5);<sep>            boolean paired = segment.indexOf(startTag) > -1;<sep><sep>            // Wrap the OmegaT tag in TMX tags in the result<sep>            result.append(segment.substring(previousMatchEnd@& match.start())); // text<sep>                                                                               // betw.<sep>                                                                               // prev.<sep>                                                                               // &<sep>                                                                               // cur.<sep>                                                                               // match<sep>            result.append(paired ? "<ept i='" : "<it pos='end' x='"); // TMX<sep>                                                                      // start<sep>                                                                      // tag +<sep>                                                                      // i/x<sep>                                                                      // attribute<sep>            result.append(tagNumber); // OmegaT tag number used as i/x attribute<sep>            result.append("'>");<sep>            result.append(tag); // OmegaT tag<sep>            result.append(paired ? "</ept>" : "</it>"); // TMX end tag<sep><sep>            // Store the current match's end positions<sep>            previousMatchEnd = match.end();<sep>        }<sep><sep>        // Append the text from the last match (end tag) to the end of the<sep>        // segment<sep>        result.append(segment.substring(previousMatchEnd@& segment.length()));<sep><sep>        // Done@& return result<sep>        return result.toString();<sep>    }

column4: public long readLong(final int numBits) {<sep>		if (numBits < 0 || numBits > Long.SIZE) {<sep>			throw new IllegalArgumentException("bits must be in range 0 ... 64!");<sep>		}<sep>		long bits = 0; // initialize all bits to zero<sep><sep>		if (currentBitIndex < 0 && (numBits & 0x7) == 0) {<sep>			// byte-wise@& no maverick bits left<sep>			for (int i = 0; i < numBits; i += 8) {<sep>				bits <<= 8;<sep>				bits |= readByte();<sep>			}<sep>		} else {<sep>			for (int i = numBits - 1; i >= 0; i--) {<sep><sep>				// check whether new byte needs to be read<sep>				if (currentBitIndex < 0) {<sep>					readCurrentByte();<sep>				}<sep><sep>				// test current bit<sep>				boolean bit = (currentByte >> currentBitIndex & 1) != 0;<sep>				if (bit) {<sep>					// set bit at i-th position<sep>					bits |= (1L << i);<sep>				}<sep><sep>				// decrease current bit index<sep>				--currentBitIndex;<sep>			}<sep>		}<sep><sep>		return bits;<sep>	}

column4: public void processSubscribe(RequestEvent requestEvent@&<sep>			ServerTransaction serverTransaction) {<sep>		SipProvider sipProvider = (SipProvider) requestEvent.getSource();<sep>		Request request = requestEvent.getRequest();<sep>		try {<sep>			logger.info("notifier: got an Subscribe sending OK");<sep>			logger.info("notifier:  " + request);<sep>			logger.info("notifier : dialog = " + requestEvent.getDialog());<sep>			EventHeader eventHeader = (EventHeader) request.getHeader(EventHeader.NAME);<sep>//			this.gotSubscribeRequest = true;<sep>			<sep>			// Always create a ServerTransaction@& best as early as possible in the code<sep>			Response response = null;<sep>			ServerTransaction st = requestEvent.getServerTransaction();			<sep>			if (st == null) {<sep>				st = sipProvider.getNewServerTransaction(request);<sep>			}<sep>			<sep>			// Check if it is an initial SUBSCRIBE or a refresh / unsubscribe<sep>			boolean isInitial = requestEvent.getDialog() == null;<sep>			if ( isInitial ) {<sep>				// JvB: need random tags to test forking<sep>				String toTag = Integer.toHexString( (int) (Math.random() * Integer.MAX_VALUE) );<sep>				response = protocolObjects.messageFactory.createResponse(202@& request);<sep>				ToHeader toHeader = (ToHeader) response.getHeader(ToHeader.NAME);<sep>				<sep>				// Sanity check: to header should not ahve a tag. Else the dialog <sep>				// should have matched<sep>				toHeader.setTag(toTag); // Application is supposed to set.<sep>				<sep>				this.dialog = st.getDialog();<sep>				// subscribe dialogs do not terminate on bye.<sep>				this.dialog.terminateOnBye(false);<sep>			} else {<sep>				response = protocolObjects.messageFactory.createResponse(202@& request);<sep>				this.dialog = st.getDialog();<sep>				// subscribe dialogs do not terminate on bye.<sep>				this.dialog.terminateOnBye(false);<sep>			}<sep><sep>			// Both 2xx response to SUBSCRIBE and NOTIFY need a Contact<sep>			Address address = protocolObjects.addressFactory.createAddress("Notifier <sip:" + System.getProperty("org.mobicents.testsuite.testhostaddr") + ">");<sep>			((SipURI)address.getURI()).setPort( sipProvider.getListeningPoint(ListeningPoint.UDP).getPort() );				<sep>			ContactHeader contactHeader = protocolObjects.headerFactory.createContactHeader(address);			<sep>			response.addHeader(contactHeader);<sep>			<sep>			// Expires header is mandatory in 2xx responses to SUBSCRIBE<sep>			ExpiresHeader expires = (ExpiresHeader) request.getHeader( ExpiresHeader.NAME );<sep>			if (expires==null) {<sep>				expires = protocolObjects.headerFactory.createExpiresHeader(30);	// rather short<sep>			}<sep>			response.addHeader( expires );<sep>			<sep>			/*<sep>			 * JvB: The SUBSCRIBE MUST be answered first. See RFC3265 3.1.6.2: <sep>			 * "[...] a NOTIFY message is always sent immediately after any 200-<sep>			 * class response to a SUBSCRIBE request"<sep>			 * <sep>			 *  Do this before creating the NOTIFY request below<sep>			 */<sep>			if(!sendNotifyBeforeResponseToSubscribe) {<sep>				logger.info("Sending Response to Subscribe");<sep>				Thread.sleep(waitBeforeFinalResponse);<sep>				st.sendResponse(response);<sep>			} else {<sep>				((SIPDialog)dialog).setLastResponse((SIPTransaction)st@& (SIPResponse)response); <sep>			}<sep>			//Thread.sleep(1000); // Be kind to implementations<sep>						<sep>			/*<sep>			 * NOTIFY requests MUST contain a "Subscription-State" header with a<sep>			 * value of "active"@& "pending"@& or "terminated". The "active" value<sep>			 * indicates that the subscription has been accepted and has been<sep>			 * authorized (in most cases; see section 5.2.). The "pending" value<sep>			 * indicates that the subscription has been received@& but that<sep>			 * policy information is insufficient to accept or deny the<sep>			 * subscription at this time. The "terminated" value indicates that<sep>			 * the subscription is not active.<sep>			 */<sep>			if(sendNotify ) {<sep>				Request notifyRequest = dialog.createRequest("NOTIFY");<sep>				<sep>				<sep>				// Mark the contact header@& to check that the remote contact is updated<sep>	//			((SipURI)contactHeader.getAddress().getURI()).setParameter("id"@&"not");<sep>				<sep>				// Initial state is pending@& second time we assume terminated (Expires==0)		<sep>				SubscriptionStateHeader sstate = protocolObjects.headerFactory.createSubscriptionStateHeader(<sep>						expires.getExpires() != 0 ? SubscriptionStateHeader.PENDING : SubscriptionStateHeader.TERMINATED );<sep>				allSubscriptionStates.add(sstate.getState().toLowerCase());<sep>				<sep>				<sep>				// Need a reason for terminated<sep>				if ( sstate.getState().equalsIgnoreCase("terminated") ) {<sep>					sstate.setReasonCode( "deactivated" );<sep>				}<sep>				<sep>				notifyRequest.addHeader(sstate);<sep>				notifyRequest.setHeader(eventHeader);<sep>				notifyRequest.setHeader(contactHeader);<sep>				// notifyRequest.setHeader(routeHeader);<sep>				ClientTransaction ct = sipProvider.getNewClientTransaction(notifyRequest);<sep>	<sep>				if(sstate.getState().equals(SubscriptionStateHeader.TERMINATED)) {<sep>					Thread.sleep(timeToWaitBetweenSubsNotify);<sep>				}<sep>				// Let the other side know that the tx is pending acceptance<sep>				//<sep>				dialog.sendRequest(ct);<sep>				logger.info("NOTIFY Branch ID " +<sep>					((ViaHeader)request.getHeader(ViaHeader.NAME)).getParameter("branch"));<sep>				logger.info("Dialog " + dialog);<sep>				logger.info("Dialog state after pending NOTIFY: " + dialog.getState());<sep>				<sep>				if (expires.getExpires() != 0) {<sep>					Thread myEventSource = new Thread(new MyEventSource(this@&eventHeader));<sep>					myEventSource.start();<sep>				}<sep>				if(sendNotifyBeforeResponseToSubscribe) {<sep>					logger.info("Sending Response to Subscribe");<sep>					Thread.sleep(waitBeforeFinalResponse);<sep>					st.sendResponse(response);<sep>				}<sep>			}<sep>		} catch (Throwable ex) {<sep>			logger.info(ex.getMessage()@& ex);<sep>		}<sep>	}

column4: public void printInstructions( String[] instructions )<sep>    {<sep>        //Clear out any current instructions<sep>        instructionsText.setText( "" );<sep><sep>        //Go down array of instruction strings<sep><sep>        String printStr@& remainingStr;<sep>        for( int i=0; i < instructions.length; i++ )<sep>        {<sep>            //chop up each into pieces maxSringLength long<sep>            remainingStr = instructions[ i ];<sep>            while( remainingStr.length() > 0 )<sep>            {<sep>                //if longer than max then chop off first max chars to print<sep>                if( remainingStr.length() >= maxStringLength )<sep>                {<sep>                    //Try to chop on a word boundary<sep>                    int posOfSpace = remainingStr.<sep>                        lastIndexOf( ' '@& maxStringLength - 1 );<sep><sep>                    if( posOfSpace <= 0 ) posOfSpace = maxStringLength - 1;<sep><sep>                    printStr = remainingStr.substring( 0@& posOfSpace + 1 );<sep>                    remainingStr = remainingStr.substring( posOfSpace + 1 );<sep>                }<sep>                //else just print<sep>                else<sep>                {<sep>                    printStr = remainingStr;<sep>                    remainingStr = "";<sep>                }<sep><sep>                instructionsText.append( printStr + " changelines " );<sep><sep>            }// while<sep><sep>        }// for<sep><sep>    }

Inline a function containing eval can have<sep>    //    large performance implications.<sep><sep>    if (!compiler.getCodingConvention().isInlinableFunction(fnNode)) {<sep>      return false;<sep>    }<sep><sep>    final String fnRecursionName = fnNode.getFirstChild().getString();<sep>    Preconditions.checkState(fnRecursionName != null);<sep><sep>    // If the function references "arguments" directly in the function<sep>    boolean referencesArguments = NodeUtil.isNameReferenced(<sep>        block@& "arguments"@& NodeUtil.MATCH_NOT_FUNCTION);<sep><sep>    // or it references "eval" or one of its names anywhere.<sep>    Predicate<Node> p = new Predicate<Node>(){<sep>      @Override<sep>      public boolean apply(Node n) {<sep>        if (n.isName()) {<sep>          return n.getString().equals("eval")<sep>            || (!fnName.isEmpty()<sep>                && n.getString().equals(fnName))<sep>            || (!fnRecursionName.isEmpty()<sep>                && n.getString().equals(fnRecursionName));<sep>        }<sep>        return false;<sep>      }<sep>    };<sep><sep>    return !referencesArguments<sep>        && !NodeUtil.has(block@& p@& Predicates.<Node>alwaysTrue());<sep>  }

LSB (least significant bit) is the last value in<sep>      // "typeInfoBits".<sep>      boolean bit = typeInfoBits.get(typeInfoBits.getSize() - 1 - i);<sep><sep>      // Type info bits at the left top corner. See 8.9 of JISX0510:2004 (p.46).<sep>      int x1 = TYPE_INFO_COORDINATES[i][0];<sep>      int y1 = TYPE_INFO_COORDINATES[i][1];<sep>      matrix.set(x1@& y1@& bit);<sep><sep>      if (i < 8) {<sep>        // Right top corner.<sep>        int x2 = matrix.getWidth() - i - 1;<sep>        int y2 = 8;<sep>        matrix.set(x2@& y2@& bit);<sep>      } else {<sep>        // Left bottom corner.<sep>        int x2 = 8;<sep>        int y2 = matrix.getHeight() - 7 + (i - 8);<sep>        matrix.set(x2@& y2@& bit);<sep>      }<sep>    }<sep>  }

column4: public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {<sep>        final JFrame f = new JFrame("XHTMLPanel");<sep>        f.addWindowListener(new WindowAdapter() {<sep>            public void windowClosing(WindowEvent e) {<sep>                System.exit(0);<sep>            }<sep>        });<sep><sep>        Container content = f.getContentPane();<sep>        content.setBackground(Color.white);<sep><sep>        // Note: we're using a layout manager that depends on the preferred size of its components.<sep>        // That's the critical point of this sample code.<sep>        content.setLayout(new FlowLayout());<sep><sep>        content.add(new JButton("Button 1"));<sep><sep>        final XHTMLPanel panel = new XHTMLPanel();<sep>        content.add(panel);<sep><sep>        content.add(new JButton("Button 2"));<sep>        content.add(new JButton("Button 3"));<sep><sep>        // Calling pack() will cause the frame and its components to be displayable (see javadoc for<sep>        // Window.pack(); this is critical for the document layout routine@& below@& to have any effect<sep>        // Note the frame doesn't need to be visible; e.g.@& we don't need to show the frame@& layout the document@&<sep>        // then resize the window; it just needs to be displayable.<sep>        f.pack();<sep><sep>        SwingUtilities.invokeAndWait(new Runnable() {<sep>            public void run() {<sep>                // Note that our document doesn't have any width constraints@& but that there is very little text<sep>                // involved@& so the document width (calculated from the content) is something reasonable for this demo.<sep>                panel.setDocumentFromString(<sep>                        "<html style='position: absolute; background-color: red;'>" +<sep>                                "    Several words that won't wrap" +<sep>                                "</html>"@&<sep>                        null@&<sep>                        new XhtmlNamespaceHandler());<sep><sep>                Dimension savedSize = panel.getSize();<sep><sep>                // Set the panel size to some artificially large size; the render engine will actually calculate<sep>                // the actual (preferred) size based on the document content. Setting it to a large size here prevents<sep>                // the document from being artificially constrained by the panel's width.<sep>                // If the document had very long runs of text@& and no width constraints@& we'd want to set the width<sep>                // to some smaller@& reasonable value (800@& 1024@& etc.). Without that@& in the absence of any other<sep>                // information@& the render engine would lay out the runs of text to as wide a space as needed to<sep>                // accomodate the text without breaks.<sep>                panel.setSize(10000@& 10000);<sep><sep>                // now we lay the document out again<sep>                panel.doDocumentLayout(panel.getGraphics());<sep><sep>                // and reset the size<sep>                panel.setSize(savedSize);<sep><sep>                f.pack();<sep>                f.setVisible(true);<sep>            }<sep>        });<sep>    }

column4: public static void main(String[] args) {<sep>        // Parse text to separate words<sep>        String INPUT_TEXT = "Hello World! Hello All! Hi World!";<sep>        // Create Multiset<sep>        Multiset<String> multiset = HashMultiset.create(Arrays.asList(INPUT_TEXT.split(" ")));<sep><sep>        // Print count words<sep>        System.out.println(multiset); // print [Hi@& Hello x 2@& World! x 2@& All!] - in random orders<sep>        // Print all unique words<sep>        System.out.println(multiset.elementSet());    // print [Hi@& Hello@& World!@& All!] - in random orders<sep><sep>        // Print count occurrences of words<sep>        System.out.println("Hello = " + multiset.count("Hello"));    // print 2<sep>        System.out.println("World = " + multiset.count("World!"));    // print 2<sep>        System.out.println("All = " + multiset.count("All!"));    // print 1<sep>        System.out.println("Hi = " + multiset.count("Hi"));    // print 1<sep>        System.out.println("Empty = " + multiset.count("Empty"));    // print 0<sep><sep>        // Print count all words<sep>        System.out.println(multiset.size());    //print 6<sep><sep>        // Print count unique words<sep>        System.out.println(multiset.elementSet().size());    //print 4<sep>    }

column4: public RPEntity getNearestEnemy(final double range) {<sep>		// create list of enemies<sep>		final List<RPEntity> enemyList = getEnemyList();<sep>		if (enemyList.isEmpty()) {<sep>			return null;<sep>		}<sep><sep>		// calculate the distance of all possible enemies<sep>		final Map<RPEntity@& Double> distances = new HashMap<RPEntity@& Double>();<sep>		for (final RPEntity enemy : enemyList) {<sep>			if (enemy == this) {<sep>				continue;<sep>			}<sep><sep>			if (enemy.isInvisibleToCreatures()) {<sep>				continue;<sep>			}<sep><sep>			final double squaredDistance = this.squaredDistance(enemy);<sep>			if (squaredDistance <= (range * range)) {<sep>				distances.put(enemy@& squaredDistance);<sep>			}<sep>		}<sep><sep>		// now choose the nearest enemy for which there is a path@& or is<sep>		// attackable otherwise<sep>		RPEntity chosen = null;<sep>		while ((chosen == null) && !distances.isEmpty()) {<sep>			double shortestDistance = Double.MAX_VALUE;<sep>			for (final Map.Entry<RPEntity@& Double> enemy : distances.entrySet()) {<sep>				final double distance = enemy.getValue();<sep>				if (distance < shortestDistance) {<sep>					chosen = enemy.getKey();<sep>					shortestDistance = distance;<sep>				}<sep>			}<sep><sep>			if (shortestDistance >= 1) {<sep>				final List<Node> path = Path.searchPath(this@& chosen@& getMovementRange());<sep>				if ((path == null) || path.isEmpty() && !strategy.canAttackNow(this@& chosen)) {<sep>					distances.remove(chosen);<sep>					chosen = null;<sep>				} else {<sep>					// set the path. if not setMovement() will search a new one<sep>					setPath(new FixedPath(path@& false));<sep>				}<sep>			}<sep>		}<sep>		// return the chosen enemy or null if we could not find one in reach<sep>		return chosen;<sep>	}

column4: @Override<sep>  public synchronized void write(byte[] source@& int offset@& int len)<sep>      throws IOException {<sep><sep>    S3ADataBlocks.validateWriteArgs(source@& offset@& len);<sep>    checkOpen();<sep>    if (len == 0) {<sep>      return;<sep>    }<sep>    S3ADataBlocks.DataBlock block = createBlockIfNeeded();<sep>    int written = block.write(source@& offset@& len);<sep>    int remainingCapacity = block.remainingCapacity();<sep>    if (written < len) {<sep>      // not everything was written the block has run out<sep>      // of capacity<sep>      // Trigger an upload then process the remainder.<sep>      LOG.debug("writing more data than block has capacity -triggering upload");<sep>      uploadCurrentBlock();<sep>      // tail recursion is mildly expensive@& but given buffer sizes must be MB.<sep>      // it's unlikely to recurse very deeply.<sep>      this.write(source@& offset + written@& len - written);<sep>    } else {<sep>      if (remainingCapacity == 0) {<sep>        // the whole buffer is done@& trigger an upload<sep>        uploadCurrentBlock();<sep>      }<sep>    }<sep>  }

column4: public boolean canAccess(Authentication user@& AccessMode mode) {<sep>        Set<String> roles = getAuthorizedRoles(mode);<sep><sep>        if (GeoServerSecurityFilterChainProxy.isSecurityEnabledForCurrentRequest() == false)<sep>            return true;<sep><sep>        // if we don't know@& we ask the parent@& otherwise we assume<sep>        // the object is unsecured<sep>        if (roles == null) {<sep>            return parent.canAccess(user@& mode);<sep>        }<sep><sep>        // if the roles is just "*" any granted authority will match<sep>        if (roles.equals(EVERYBODY)) return true;<sep><sep>        // let's scan thru the the authorities granted to the user and<sep>        // see if he matches any of the write roles<sep>        if (user == null || user.getAuthorities() == null) return false;<sep>        // look for a match on the roles@& using the "root" rules as well (root can do everything)<sep>        for (GrantedAuthority authority : user.getAuthorities()) {<sep>            final String userRole = authority.getAuthority();<sep>            if (roles.contains(userRole) || ROOT_ROLE.equals(userRole)) return true;<sep>        }<sep>        return false;<sep>    }

column4: private static ClassLoader combineLoadersOf(Class<?> first@& Class<?>... others) {<sep>        List<ClassLoader> loaders = new ArrayList<ClassLoader>();<sep>        <sep>        addIfNewElement(loaders@& first.getClassLoader());<sep>        for (Class<?> c : others) {<sep>            addIfNewElement(loaders@& c.getClassLoader());<sep>        }<sep>        <sep>        // To support Eclipse Plug-in tests.<sep>        // In an Eclipse plug-in@& jMock itself will not be on the system class loader<sep>        // but in the class loader of the plug-in.<sep>        //<sep>        // Note: I've been unable to reproduce the error in jMock's test suite.<sep>        addIfNewElement(loaders@& SearchingClassLoader.class.getClassLoader());<sep>        <sep>        // To support the Maven Surefire plugin.<sep>        // Note: I've been unable to reproduce the error in jMock's test suite.<sep>        addIfNewElement(loaders@& currentThread().getContextClassLoader());<sep><sep>        //Had to comment that out because it didn't work with in-container Spring tests<sep>        //addIfNewElement(loaders@& ClassLoader.getSystemClassLoader());<sep>        <sep>        return combine(loaders);<sep>    }

column4: public void testEmptyRightmostLeaf() throws Exception {<sep>        // Trace latch conflicts to see that we exercise the code path that<sep>        // handles repositioning after waiting for a latch when moving away<sep>        // from an empty leaf at the far-right end of the B-tree. When this<sep>        // code is exercised@& we'll see "Restart scan from rightmost leaf"<sep>        // printed to derby.log.<sep>        setTraceFlag("BTreeMaxScan.latchConflict");<sep><sep>        setAutoCommit(false);<sep><sep>        Statement s = createStatement();<sep>        s.execute("create table t(x int)");<sep><sep>        // Insert a couple pages worth of rows.<sep>        PreparedStatement ins = prepareStatement("insert into t values ?");<sep>        for (int i = 1; i <= 800; i++) {<sep>            ins.setInt(1@& i);<sep>            ins.executeUpdate();<sep>        }<sep><sep>        s.execute("create index i on t(x)");<sep><sep>        commit();<sep><sep>        // Now start four threads. Two scanning the B-tree in the forward<sep>        // direction@& and two scanning in the backward direction (max scans).<sep>        // These threads should not interfere with each other.<sep>        String forwardSQL = "select x from t --derby-properties index=i";<sep>        String backwardSQL = "select max(x) from t --derby-properties index=i";<sep><sep>        final PreparedStatement[] pss = {<sep>            openDefaultConnection().prepareStatement(forwardSQL)@&<sep>            openDefaultConnection().prepareStatement(forwardSQL)@&<sep>            openDefaultConnection().prepareStatement(backwardSQL)@&<sep>            openDefaultConnection().prepareStatement(backwardSQL)@&<sep>        };<sep><sep>        final Exception[] exceptions = new Exception[pss.length];<sep><sep>        final Thread[] threads = new Thread[pss.length];<sep><sep>        final AtomicInt threadCount = new AtomicInt();<sep><sep>        for (int i = 0; i < pss.length; i++) {<sep>            final int threadNo = i;<sep>            // Set the isolation level to read uncommitted so that the scans<sep>            // don't take any locks. We do this because we want to test latch<sep>            // conflicts@& and if the scans take read locks@& they'll spend most<sep>            // of the time waiting for the write thread to release its locks.<sep>            pss[i].getConnection().setTransactionIsolation(<sep>                    Connection.TRANSACTION_READ_UNCOMMITTED);<sep>            threads[i] = new Thread() {<sep>                public void run() {<sep>                    try {<sep>                        for (int j = 0; j < 1000; j++) {<sep>                            ResultSet rs = pss[threadNo].executeQuery();<sep>                            if (threadNo < 2) {<sep>                                // This is a full forward scan (SELECT *) of<sep>                                // the B-tree@& so expect it to see between 400<sep>                                // and 800 rows.<sep>                                int rowCount = JDBC.assertDrainResults(rs);<sep>                                if (rowCount < 400 || rowCount > 800) {<sep>                                    fail("Unexpected row count: " + rowCount);<sep>                                }<sep>                            } else {<sep>                                // This is a max scan@& so expect a single<sep>                                // row that contains a value between 400 and<sep>                                // 800.<sep>                                assertTrue(rs.next());<sep>                                int max = rs.getInt(1);<sep>                                if (max < 400 || max > 800) {<sep>                                    fail("Unexpected max value: " + max);<sep>                                }<sep>                                assertFalse(rs.next());<sep>                                rs.close();<sep>                            }<sep>                        }<sep>                    } catch (Exception e) {<sep>                        exceptions[threadNo] = e;<sep>                    } finally {<sep>                        threadCount.decrement();<sep>                    }<sep>                }<sep>            };<sep>            threads[i].start();<sep>            threadCount.increment();<sep>        }<sep><sep>        // As long as the scanner threads are running@& periodically delete<sep>        // and re-insert the last 400 rows. This empties the rightmost leaf<sep>        // page(s) and makes it possible for the scanners to encounter the<sep>        // situation where they need to reposition after a latch conflict<sep>        // while being positioned on an empty page with no saved position. The<sep>        // post-commit worker will eventually remove the pointers to the empty<sep>        // leaf@& so we need to do this repeatedly and hope that the timing<sep>        // will be right at least once so that we exercise the desired path.<sep>        PreparedStatement deleteRows =<sep>                prepareStatement("delete from t where x > 400");<sep>        PreparedStatement insertRows =<sep>                prepareStatement("insert into t select x+400 from t");<sep>        while (threadCount.get() > 0) {<sep>            // Delete rows in range [401@& 800].<sep>            assertEquals("deleted rows"@& 400@& deleteRows.executeUpdate());<sep>            commit();<sep><sep>            // Sleep a little while so that we don't fill the empty page<sep>            // before the scanners have seen it.<sep>            Thread.sleep(100L);<sep><sep>            // Re-insert rows in range [401@& 800].<sep>            assertEquals("inserted rows"@& 400@& insertRows.executeUpdate());<sep>            commit();<sep>        }<sep><sep>        for (int i = 0; i < pss.length; i++) {<sep>            threads[i].join();<sep>            pss[i].getConnection().close();<sep>        }<sep><sep>        for (int i = 0; i < exceptions.length; i++) {<sep>            if (exceptions[i] != null) {<sep>                throw exceptions[i];<sep>            }<sep>        }<sep><sep>        dropTable("T");<sep>        commit();<sep>    }

column4: protected boolean isBetterLocation(Location location) {<sep>        if (currentBestLocation == null) {<sep>            // A new location is always better than no location<sep>            return true;<sep>        }<sep><sep>        // Check whether the new location fix is newer or older<sep>        long timeDelta = location.getTime() - currentBestLocation.getTime();<sep>        boolean isSignificantlyNewer = timeDelta > TWO_MINUTES;<sep>        boolean isSignificantlyOlder = timeDelta < -TWO_MINUTES;<sep>        boolean isNewer = timeDelta > 0;<sep><sep>        // If it's been more than two minutes since the current location@& use the new location<sep>        // because the user has likely moved<sep>        if (isSignificantlyNewer) {<sep>            return true;<sep>            // If the new location is more than two minutes older@& it must be worse<sep>        } else if (isSignificantlyOlder) {<sep>            return false;<sep>        }<sep><sep>        // Check whether the new location fix is more or less accurate<sep>        int accuracyDelta = (int) (location.getAccuracy() - currentBestLocation.getAccuracy());<sep>        boolean isLessAccurate = accuracyDelta > 0;<sep>        boolean isMoreAccurate = accuracyDelta < 0;<sep>        boolean isSignificantlyLessAccurate = accuracyDelta > 200;<sep><sep>        // Check if the old and new location are from the same provider<sep>        boolean isFromSameProvider = isSameProvider(location.getProvider()@&<sep>                currentBestLocation.getProvider());<sep><sep>        // Determine location quality using a combination of timeliness and accuracy<sep>        if (isMoreAccurate) {<sep>            return true;<sep>        } else if (isNewer && !isLessAccurate) {<sep>            return true;<sep>        } else if (isNewer && !isSignificantlyLessAccurate && isFromSameProvider) {<sep>            return true;<sep>        }<sep>        return false;<sep>    }

column4: public static int calculateInSampleSize(final BitmapFactory.Options options@& final int reqWidth@&<sep>            final int reqHeight) {<sep>        // Raw height and width of image<sep>        final int height = options.outHeight;<sep>        final int width = options.outWidth;<sep>        int inSampleSize = 1;<sep><sep>        if (height > reqHeight || width > reqWidth) {<sep><sep>            // Calculate ratios of height and width to requested height and<sep>            // width<sep>            final int heightRatio = Math.round((float) height / (float) reqHeight);<sep>            final int widthRatio = Math.round((float) width / (float) reqWidth);<sep><sep>            // Choose the smallest ratio as inSampleSize value@& this will<sep>            // guarantee<sep>            // a final image with both dimensions larger than or equal to the<sep>            // requested height and width.<sep>            inSampleSize = heightRatio < widthRatio ? heightRatio : widthRatio;<sep>        }<sep><sep>        return inSampleSize;<sep>    }

i < parameterTypes.length; i++) {<sep>            Class<?> parameterType = parameterTypes[i];<sep>            for (Iterator<Element> iterator = nodes.iterator(); iterator.hasNext();) {<sep>                Element element = iterator.next();<sep>                // first we check if the parameter index is specified<sep>                Element match = getMatch(element@& "parameter[@index='" + i + "']");<sep>                if (match != null<sep>                // we check if the type is specified and matches<sep>                    && DOMUtils.getAttributeValueEmptyNull(match@& "class") != null<sep>                    // if it doesn't match@& then we can definitely rule out<sep>                    // this result<sep>                    && !DOMUtils.getAttributeValueEmptyNull(match@& "class").equals(parameterType.getName())) {<sep><sep>                    iterator.remove();<sep>                }<sep>            }<sep>        }<sep>        // if we have just one node left@& then it has to be the best match<sep>        if (nodes.size() == 1) {<sep>            return nodes.get(0);<sep>        }<sep>        // all remaining definitions could apply@& so we need to now pick the<sep>        // best one<sep>        // the best one is the one with the most parameters specified<sep>        Element bestCandidate = null;<sep>        int highestSpecified = 0;<sep>        for (Iterator<Element> iterator = nodes.iterator(); iterator.hasNext();) {<sep>            Element element = iterator.next();<sep><sep>            List<Element> params = DOMUtils.getChildrenWithName(element@& ""@& "parameter");<sep>            int availableParameters = params.size();<sep>            if (availableParameters > highestSpecified) {<sep>                bestCandidate = element;<sep>                highestSpecified = availableParameters;<sep>            }<sep>        }<sep>        return bestCandidate;<sep>    }
